ğŸ“„ 2. Project Overview
The Sustainable Smart City Assistant is an AI-driven application developed to support smart city planning and governance. The assistant uses the IBM Granite LLM model for providing intelligent responses, extracting insights from documents, and addressing citizen queries related to sustainable urban living.
________________________________________
ğŸ¯ 3. Objective
The goal of this project is to enhance the quality of urban governance and citizen engagement by leveraging a state-of-the-art Large Language Model (LLM). The assistant aims to:
â€¢	Simplify access to sustainable city policies and documents.
â€¢	Assist citizens by answering questions related to city planning.
â€¢	Enable quick and intelligent insights for city administrators.
________________________________________
